\Bbb {Z} /p\Bbb{Z} [x] / (x^2+1)
ax+b
x^2 + 1 = 0
x^2 = -1 = p-1
(ax+b)(cx+d) =(acx^2 + bd) + x(ad+bc) = (-ac+bd)+x(ad+bc)
\Bbb {Z} /p\Bbb{Z} [x] / (x^2+1)  =  \Bbb {Z} /p\Bbb{Z}[i]
\Bbb {Z} /5\Bbb{Z} [x] / (x^2+1) = [\Bbb {Z} /5\Bbb{Z} [x] / (x-2)] \times [\Bbb {Z} /5\Bbb{Z} [x] / (x-3)] = \Bbb {Z} /5\Bbb{Z} \times \Bbb {Z} /5\Bbb{Z}
\,x^2+1=(x+2)(x+3)\pmod 5\Longrightarrow \Bbb F_5[x]/\langle\,x^2+1\,\rangle\,
\Bbb F_5[x]/\langle\,(x+2)(x+3)\,\rangle\cong \Bbb F_5[x]/\langle x+2\rangle\times\Bbb F_5[x]/\langle x+3\rangle\cong \Bbb F_5\times\Bbb F_5
\,\Bbb F_5:=\Bbb Z/5\Bbb Z\,
